NOVEL CONTRIBUTIONS PROTECTED UNDER THIS LICENSE:

This license protects the following original intellectual contributions
of this work, each of which is an original research contribution:

  1. The closed-loop two-stage AI architecture integrating a real-time
     XGBoost attacker profiler with a DQN adaptive deception agent.

  2. The state-conditioned reward function using live XGBoost probability
     outputs (P(bot), P(sk), P(adv)) as dynamic reward multipliers for the
     DQN policy — not previously described in published literature.

  3. The curiosity-driven per-action intrinsic exploration bonus applied
     to honeypot deception policy training.

  4. The action synergy chain mechanism: delay_response → change_filesystem
     → inject_fake_data cascading reward structure.

  5. The multi-source honeypot preprocessing pipeline merging 8 heterogeneous
     data sources into a unified 45-feature schema across 32,971,269 samples.

  6. The three-version iterative DQN training methodology with documented
     policy collapse diagnosis and theoretical analysis.

